  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C).",
    "Chop the fennel bulb into wedges and the onion in half.",
    "Drizzle olive oil over all vegetables and toss with salt, pepper, paprika, cumin seeds, coriander powder, and turmeric powder.",
    "Roast vegetables for about 20-25 minutes or until tender. Let cool slightly.",
    "Stir-fry the cooled vegetables in a pan with nutritional yeast, tomato paste, and remaining olive oil over medium heat for 3-4 minutes.",
    "Mix in sesame seeds to coat evenly.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish or main course."
